@node Musicreviews
@title "Music Reviews "



             HARDSEQUENCER - Move Fast EP
            ***************************Fire Rec.****
            Again Hardsequencer brought us a very
            interesting piece of vinyl. 4 Trax with
            again Amiga-like Tunes are on this Rec..
            'From the Ear to the brain' is the new  
            Clubhit from this EP, but the others are
            cool too. But, the I prefer the last
            Hardsequencer one.         7 of 10 [SMC]
                                                    
            PINK VINYL WITH GLOBE ON LABEL ?????
            *********Dance International Records****
            I don't know group and title of this    
            Rec., but I like it anyway. On Logo Side
            we have a 25Min Acid-styled 303 Track.
            On Info Side 3 Trax of different and
            interesting 303 Compositions. No Hits,  
            but with monotone power.
                                       7 of 10 [SMC]

             KOSMIK KOMMANDO - A303 The South West
            *************************Acid Lab UK****
            This yellow-covered EP has 5 Trax on it.
            There are no names of songs on it, but  
            Number 2 of Yellow Side is megafast with
            confusing Synth-Sequences. The other    
            songs I would describe as Fast-Deep-Acid
            Some of them are played on last Raves
            here in Munich.            8 of 10 [SMC]

             LUNATIC ASYLUM - Meltdown Mixes (+CD)  
            ***REC.= Fnac/Paris****CD=Sony Music****
            5 Mixes of one of the Hits of this year.
            Unfortunately the first 4 trax, remixed 
            by the MOVER are quite the same, not bad
            but not having the power of the original
            mix found on this CD too as Mix 5. So if
            ya haven't Meltdown yet - buy, otherwise
            get the ALSO CD or Trancemaster 6 (with
            Meltdown on it!). 9(V) 7(I-IV) /10 [SMC]


             At last of my critics (few this time!)
             I give you a list of OLDER Recs you
             should get if you like TRANCE music:   

             VERNONs Wonderland - Sven Vaeth Rmxs
               (EYE Q Records   *    8 of 10)

             VISIONS OF SHIVA - how much can u take
               (MFS Records     *    7 of 10)
                                                    
                BALLOONS      - Fluxland EP
               (Rule Music/Sony *    9 of 10)       
                                                    
               ENERGY 52 - Cafe del Mar (+Rmxs)
               (EYE Q Records   *    9 of 10)

               INTERACTIVE - Koma (on AMOK CD)      
               (Technoland      *    8 of 10)
                                                    
             and of coz:

               CJ BOLLAND - The 4 Sign EP  (9 of 10)
               (R & S Records)

             and (SUPERB!) :

                  4 VOICE - especially following
                            trax:

                          - MUSIC HYPNOTISES (10/10)

                          - ETERNAL SPIRIT   (10/10)

              You can't do Trance much better than
                4Voice did, that's why 10/10 !

                [^^^ SMC ^^^]

----------------
		And now some lines about Trance-
		master 5(The Hardtrance Experience)
		typed by Toxic/Abyss...

		Ok lets go:

		1.Intertribal-Trance Intro
		--------------------------
		This one is very short and some-
		thing like a tribal dance. Ya
		can hear men and women crying
		nearly as they fuck together.
		Nothing special-just a intro!

		2.Capricorn-20 Hz
		-----------------
		First ya hear some bell-samples,
		then some confusing drumparts.
		I think, they are awful at all!
		After that a real nice morphing
		part about 1 Minute the bell
		turns back again. All in all
		a really bad song. Its not
		trance, its a accident in elec-
		tronic music.
		2 of 10 points. Ugliest Song
		on disc.

		3.Dance2Trance-Take a free fall
		  (Paul van Dyk Remix)
		-------------------------------
		The song begins with a cool
		pianopart and some cool morph-
		samples. This song is a real
		standart trancepiece. Nothing
		special but still cool.
		7 of 10 points.

		4.Datura-Yerba Del Diabolo
		--------------------------
		At the beginning ya hear a
		female voice calling some
		words. The whole song is one
		of those commercial breaks
		in your head. I dont like it
		very much. Only standart.
		5 of 10 points.

		5.Komakino-Beyond your Dreams
		  (Mikrobots Remix)
		-----------------------------
		This song also begins with a
		piano and a mystic voice
		calling the title. Very cool
		bass-samles. I like them.
		A very long pushing song with
		cool piano parts between.
		7 of 10 points.

		6.Speedy J.-Ginger
		------------------
		Begins with a hard bassdrum
		and some samples like in
		an Alienstrip. Boring song
		with standart effekts.
		5 of 10 points.

		7.Manitou-Ever means Never
		--------------------------
		Joh, thats it.
		At first a real cool chorus
		about 30 seconds, then
		suddenly a killerbass and
		some confuse electronic
		cries. After that changing
		to the slow pianopart again.
		Very cool arranged song.
		8 of 10 points.

		8.Lawnmover-In Danger:Mix 1
		---------------------------
		Whole song just like an
		intropart. Nothing special.
		6 of 10 points.

		9.Cyberia-Doors 1
		-----------------
		Something like an organsong
		mixed with an hard bass and
		som strings. Nice to hear,
		but please not very often.
		6 of 10 points.

		10.Zero Gravity-Neural Dec.
		---------------------------
		Hard bassdrum. Good samples.
		Nice arrangement. Much breaks.
		Just listen to it.
		7 of 10 points.

		11.Gatorades-Dark Piano
		-----------------------
		Absolutely the best song on
		this sampler. Begins with
		a distorted piano.Soon
		followed by an hard bassdrum
		and special deep morphparts.
		Killersong. Kicks yar ass.
		9 of 10 points.

		12.Psilocybin-TLL Core
		----------------------
		Not a standart trancesong.
		Just like the psychedelic
		electric tunes. Just like
		breakbeat.
		Nice to hear.
		7 of 10 points.


		Saldo:
		One of the best trance-
		sampler available on CD.
		Bye or die.

		[DONE by TOXIC of ABYSS]



@endnode
